  "body": "In order to test the HTTP JSONRPC functionality of my code, I'm looking to run a Buidler EVM server (like `buidler node`) programmatically. After looking at the source code for a bit, it seems I can use something like this:\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nimport buidler from '@nomiclabs/buidler';\r\nimport { JsonRpcServer } from '@nomiclabs/buidler/internal/buidler-evm/jsonrpc/server';\r\n\r\nconst server = new JsonRpcServer({\r\n  hostname: '127.0.0.1',\r\n  port: 8545,\r\n  provider: buidler.network.provider\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut I assume this is not a public API. It would be nice if there was a better way to do something like this.",
